-- static
-- Static variables: Shared by all object of the class.
-- Static Methods: Can be called without creating an object.

-- Static Blocks: Used to initialized static variables when the class is first loaded.






-- Default Methods
-- Methods with a body that use the default keyword. that will implement by the
interface.
-- static methods: methods with a body the belongs to the interface name itself not
object

-- why it is used?(default)
-- backward compatibility:
if you have interface tht use by the 1,000 class and you need to add new feature,
making it default prevents all 1,000 class from crashing.



-- why it is used?(static)
-- Memory Efficiency: Instead of giving every object its own copy, you store it
once.

-- Utility: It allows you to create 'Helper' functions that don't need object data


